1. User Input (Scanner Class)
import java.util.Scanner;

2. Creating Scanner Object
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

3. Reading Integer
float salary = sc.nextFloat();

4. Reading Double
double price = sc.nextDouble();

5. Reading Character
char grade = sc.next().charAt(0);

6. Reading String (Single Word)
String name = sc.next();

7. Reading Full Sentence
String address = sc.nextLine();

8. Difference Between next() and nextLine()
next()	nextLine()
Reads one word	Reads complete line
Stops at space	Reads until Enter
Returns first word only	Returns whole sentence

Example:
Input - Priyanshi Rajpoot

String name = sc.next();

output - Priyanshi


9. Why nextLine() Gets Skipped?
int age = sc.nextInt();

String name = sc.nextLine();

Problem:
name becomes empty.

Solution

int age = sc.nextInt();

sc.nextLine();

String name = sc.nextLine();


10. Closing Scanner
sc.close();
